<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Puppet Program Coordinator</a></h2>

<p><strong>POSITION:</strong> Puppet Program Coordinator<br />
  <strong>SUPERVISOR: </strong>Gretchen Godfrey<br />
  <strong>STATUS:</strong> 60-75%, Exempt</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>Organize and lead COUNT ME IN and Kids Against Bullying volunteers
  <ul>
    <li>Recruit and train volunteers to present puppet shows.</li>
    <li>Schedule volunteers.</li>
  </ul></li>
  <li>Work with schools to schedule COUNT ME IN and Kids Against Bullying puppet shows.</li>
  <li>Memorize scripts, present educational puppet shows, and transport puppets and show materials as needed.</li>
  <li>Update all scripts and resource materials.</li>
  <li>Assist with marketing the PACER puppets and materials nationally.</li>
  <li>Maintain puppets, supplies, and equipment.</li>
  <li>Keep records, write reports, and maintain all COUNT ME IN and Kids Against Bullying correspondence.</li>
  <li>Make presentations on the project to other groups.</li>
  <li>Other tasks as may be required.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul type="disc">
  <li>Public speaking experience</li>
  <li>Excellent organizational skills and attention to detail </li>
  <li>Flexibility in daily schedule</li>
  <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</li>
  <li>Experience working with children</li>
  <li>Ability to lift and transport puppets and related items, up to approximately 25 lbs. on a regular basis; have Driver&rsquo;s License and vehicle for travel in greater metro area</li>
  <li>Ability to prioritize and meet deadlines</li>
  <li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills </li>
  <li>Proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite, specifically Word and      Outlook</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Desired qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul type="disc">
  <li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree </li>
  <li>Experience creating and presenting information to children</li>
  <li>Experience in training and working with volunteers</li>
  <li>Knowledge of issues related to persons with disabilities and      bullying prevention</li>
</ul>
<p>Parents  of children with disabilities are encouraged to apply. Salary will be based on experience and qualifications.</p>
